      void createCardPanel()
      The createCardPanel method creates the CardPanels to hold the representations of the player's decks and the cards that they have down on the field.

      The createGamePanel method creates the overall panel for the game itself, including a layout of cards for each player, with an overall panel to hold those.

      The createTitlePanel method creates a panel for the title of the game, then creates a label for the title and adds it.
      void winnerText()
      The winnerText method calls the getWarWinner method from the War class in order to determine what message to display, based on who won the game.

    • Method Detail

      • createGamePanel

        public void createGamePanel()
        The createGamePanel method creates the overall panel for the game itself, including a layout of cards for each player, with an overall panel to hold those. It then sets their backgrounds and adds them to the game panel. It also creates the button to activate the game, and the button Listener to respond to it.

      • createCardPanel

        public void createCardPanel()
        The createCardPanel method creates the CardPanels to hold the representations of the player's decks and the cards that they have down on the field. It then sets their background colors and adds them to the overall panel for the game itself.

      • createTitlePanel

        public void createTitlePanel()
        The createTitlePanel method creates a panel for the title of the game, then creates a label for the title and adds it.

      • createPlayerLabels

        public void createPlayerLabels()
        The createPlayerLabels method creates the names for each player and the message that displays who the winner of the war was.

      • winnerText

        public void winnerText()
        The winnerText method calls the getWarWinner method from the War class in order to determine what message to display, based on who won the game.
